n intensive care. The median age of those infected in August is 36. NAN Vanguard UK on Sunday reported 170 more coronavirus deaths -- its lowest number since late March, when lockdown restrictions were introduced, although the figures from Northern Ireland were not included. Prime Minister Boris Johnson meanwhile acknowledged public frustration with the restrictions imposed to fight the virus. The coronavirus deaths take the… May 17, 2020 In "Foreign" GlaxoSmithKline, GSK, world's largest vaccine maker, has said there will be no mass coronavirus vaccine until late next year, just as Pfizer said its COVID-19 jab could be ready by this autumn (from September). Emma Walmsley, Chief Executive of GSK, said millions of doses would not be produced until the… April 29, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates" The European Commission and German biotech firm, CureVac, on Thursday said they had concluded a first round of talks for the supply of no less than 225 million doses of a potential COVID-19 vaccine to EU member states. The EU’s executive arm is also in talks with Johnson & Johnson… August 21, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates"